rComments: inspirational prof
amazing professor and person
She's an excellent prof and cares a lot about her students. Her lectures were clear and she made it interesting, I highly recommend this course

Professor Malti is amazing! You can tell that she is passionate about the material. Her lectures are detailed and informative. She made a late lecture interesting and entertaining, which can be hard! I would definitely enroll in another course taught by her
I highly recommend this course, it's incredibly interesting.
Prof. Malti is an amazing lecturer and explains concepts very clearly. The tests arent easy but doable. Overall, a great course.
she's a great prof
Content is very interesting and she's a nice prof, but hard to get a B and material is tested very specifically.

This course tests are 50% lecture and 50% textbook. Need to read textbook thoroughly and pay attention in lecture and make good notes.  Tests are majorly MC and so if you don't read textbook carefully, you may not do well. 50 marks. Prof is not very clear of expectations. Lots of discussion. Course is almost self-taught in some aspects.
Lectures seemed fast-paced but the quality of the instruction was good. She was very passionate about the material.
She is a good prof, very organized, and really knows what she is talking about. The material is interesting and tests are fair if you study hard

This class had the most boring, long lectures. Despite understanding the material, the tests (and perhaps the exam) were SO HARD to do well on, she tested like the most minor thing in the book. Glad to be done with this boring, long class.
Great Prof

The most frustrating professor I've had ever! Won't give any guidance with regards to the course material, standard answer when you go to her for help is: "read everything" and she means EVERYTHING. Tests are about your ability to memorize facts and not understanding of concepts. Read the textbook inside out if you want an A.

I don't know why her reviews are so great, she is absolutely useless. The material is SO interesting and she just makes it dull by reading off slides, then adding pointless demos and videos. It is also very difficult to understand her. I've attended the majority of the lectures, but it is such a waste of time. You learn way more from the textbook.

She is honestly such a great prof. I love her enthusiasm, its something you rarely see. I went to every class because she made it so much fun! Loved her lectures! Tests were fair as well! Assignments were super easy!
I love her! She's awesome, always enthusiastic, cheerful and friendly during lectures. Her tests are very fair. Always tried to make class fun and interactive with her activities.
great professor. MC tests with one SA - easy. very engaging and has very useful videos for examples. very interesting course and would recommend it!! easy 4.0 if you do your readings!!

I absolutely found Malti's class the most rewarding and enjoyable; always was in the front and I was highly engaged every day. I look forward to be part of her future 3rd year classes. She's also very passionate about her work which shows in her lectures and makes it much more enjoyable. <3

BEST PROF EVER!!! Looked forward to every lecture. Very approachable and super nice. Lectures are very interactive and I learned a lot! Tests are fair. I'm looking forward to having her as a prof again :)

AMAZING PROF! She is an amazing person who is truly passionate about what she does! Lectures are great and clear to the point and tests are very fair! Overall, I would recommend her class to ANYONE and look forward having her in other upper year courses

AWESOME prof-BRILLIANT! LOVE HER! Her passion for psych is inspiring. Totally approachable & open to feedback/questions. Slides clear & concise, tests extremely fair. Read text, attend lectures, study-you should be fine. Engaging course, you will learn A LOT. Videos/demos clarify concepts. Looked forward to every lecture. VERY HIGHLY RECOMMENDED!
Passionate about her work. Follows the textbook, the amount of videos which are shown are not really needed (but they are fun to watch). Hard to understand because of her accent. Be prepared to read.
